g.aria-label: Cost of Wave Energy by Stage

MWDeploymentLCOE/kWhSubsidy: $5.5BAchieving the full potential of wave energy will require moreresearch and development. We estimate that $2.5 billion would beneeded, the same that the U.S. Department of Energy spent from1978 to 2014 on R&D on wind energy. We estimate an additional$300 million of investment is needed to bring partial scale projectsto full commercial scale. Based on a learning rate such thatdoubling the deployment of wave technology should bring theprice down by 15%, we estimate that $5.5 billion of public subsidywould bring wave technology to a price of 6 /kWh, at which pointit could compete in coastal electricity markets.Coggins, A.
